i just got my braces off a few days ago and they gave me my retainer yesterday i was wondering if it is really neccesary to wear the retainer for hours straight for the next few months or is it okay to take it out for a little while for a break i wear it to sleep and usually a few hours during the day is that okay or should i wear it more often you should wear it as much as possible but to be honest with you you will know if your teeth start to move when the retainer is tighter than usual when you put it in at that point you need to wear all the time my daughter has been out of braces for years and she never wore her retainer all the time she would wear it home but never out if she forgot to put it in for a few days she would know it when she did put it in and then just wear it untill it felt right again good luck and be careful after all those years of braces you don't want to have your teeth move back be very observant and you will know Dental brace Drill bit Social rule Cliff Richard Daylight saving time Shaggy dog story Paul Is Dead Orthodontics Sydney Riot of 1879 Carpal tunnel syndrome Donald Neilson The Ashlee Simpson Show Upholstery Michael Garibaldi New York Giants Nine Inch Nails Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an American and British English differences Mickey Mantle AFI 100 Years series Steven Wright The Citadel (Military College) Good Morning, Vietnam Kurt Angle The Amber Spyglass The Amazing Race The Care Bears Adventure in Wonderland Frankie Laine Hipparchus (astronomer) Singlish The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Tooth Pitaten USS Waters (DD-115) 613 mitzvot Equine conformation Ethics Charles Peace The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Mattress Tooth enamel Humphrey Bogart Bj__rn Borg Avenue Q Characters in the Smurfs Procrastination Big Brother (Australian TV series) Milton H. Erickson Diving E. E. Cummings Time Dentistry Julian day Skinhead Scoliosis New England Patriots Poker jargon The Grim Adventures of Billy 